-- Peru Stocks: Ferreyros, Maple, Panoro,Relapasa, Siderperu
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-06-18T21:10:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-18/peru-stocks-ferreyros-maple-energy-relapasa-siderperu.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the market close.  The  Lima  General Index rose for the first time in seven
days, gaining 0.4 percent to 20,714.60. The MSCI All Peru Capped
Index climbed 1 percent to 2,745.64.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of
Gerdau SA known as Siderperu, rose 2.9 percent to 72 centimos as
investors bet the  construction industry  will expand on increased
public spending on infrastructure, said Inteligo SAB analyst
Rodrigo Zuazo.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., gained 1.5 percent to 2.69 soles.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, climbed 1.8 percent to 57 cents as copper
advanced for a fourth day in  New York .  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, rose 1.5 percent to 69 cents.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, fell 1.5 percent to 64 centimos as
crude slumped in New York.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, slid 0.9 percent to $1.07.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
